在[[人类学|人类学]]，'''特权'''是特殊的权利、优势或豁免权，只有特定的个人或群体才能获得或享有。<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://en.oxforddictionaries.com/definition/privilege|title=Privilege | Definition of privilege in English by Oxford Dictionaries|accessdate=2019-02-04|archive-date=2019-03-17|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190317061206/https://en.oxforddictionaries.com/definition/privilege|dead-url=no}}</ref>在[[社会学|社会学中]] ，特权指的是[[感知|可观察到的]]仅对特定个人或群体适用的权利或优势。该术语通常用于描述[[社会不平等|社会不平等]]的现象，特别是关于[[年龄歧视|年龄]]、[[身心障礙|残疾]]、[[人種|种族或种族类别]]、[[社會性別|性别]]、[[性別認同|性别认同]]、[[性取向|性取向]]、[[宗教|宗教]]和[[社会阶级|社会阶层]]等多种不平等方面 。<ref name=":0">{{Cite book|title=Geographies of Privilege|last=Twine|first=France Winddance|publisher=Routledge|year=2013|isbn=978-0415519618|location=|pages=8–10}}</ref>两个比较常见的社会不平等现象涉及获得高等教育和住房的机会。<ref name=":0" />在该术语的较新用法下，特权也可以有情感或心理方面的含义，用来描述自我认可和个人自信，或具有社会归属感或价值感。<ref name=":1">{{Cite book|title=Privilege: A Reader|last=Kimmel|first=Michael S.|publisher=Westview Press|year=2009|isbn=978-0813344263|location=|pages=1, 5, 13–26}}</ref>它起初是一个学术概念，但后来在学术界之外被更广泛地引用。<ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/society/2013/jun/05/check-your-privilege-means|title=Check your privilege! Whatever that means|first=Hadley|author=Hadley Freeman|date=2013-06-05|work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|accessdate=2018-11-02|archive-date=2018-08-03|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20180803202521/https://www.theguardian.com/society/2013/jun/05/check-your-privilege-means|dead-url=no}}</ref><ref>{{Cite news|url=https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2017/dec/27/check-your-privilege-racism-sexism-education-income|title=‘Check your privilege’ used to annoy me. Now I get it|author=Gaby Hinsliff|first=Gaby|work=[[The_Guardian|The Guardian]]|date=2017-12-27|accessdate=2018-11-02|archive-date=2018-11-01|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181101180332/https://www.theguardian.com/commentisfree/2017/dec/27/check-your-privilege-racism-sexism-education-income|dead-url=no}}</ref>

